title.rendered: There’s more to it: Warner on captaincy ban not just being a result of sandpaper scandal

content.rendered:
Australia’s left-handed opener batter David Warner has claimed that the lifetime captaincy ban imposed on him by Cricket Australia is not just a result of the 2018 sandpaper scandal. He said that there was “more to it”, including 2017’s dispute between the country’s cricket board and players over pay scale. At that time, Cricket Australia reportedly threatened players over a pay dispute. As per the report, Warner is set to discuss with CA to end his above lifetime leadership ban in the national team.

 However, the 35-year-old left-handed opener has been included in the Australia squad for the T20 World Cup 2022.


Here below is the Australia squad for the T20 World Cup 2022:

Australia’s squad for T20 World Cup 2022: Aaron Finch (C), Pat Cummins (VC), Ashton Agar, Tim David, Josh Hazlewood, Josh Inglis, Mitchell Marsh, Glenn Maxwell, Kane Richardson, Steven Smith, Mitchell Starc, Marcus Stoinis, Matthew Wade, David Warner, Adam Zampa.

Read also:Sachin Tendulkar shares video of his special method to clean bat grip, criticized for wasting water
